<h3>WebSocket Event Stream: {{ channel }}</h3>
<p>Establishes a live WebSocket connection for resource events on channel <code>{{ channel }}</code>.</p>


<p>Below are the expected payload types. <strong>Incoming Payload Model</strong> is what clients should send inside <code>Event.payload</code>, and the <strong>Outgoing Payload Model</strong> is what the server will broadcast in <code>Event.payload</code>.</p>
<p style="font-size:0.95em; color:#444"><strong>Note:</strong> If the <em>Incoming Payload Model</em> displays <code>-</code> there is no client-facing input handler for this event. These events are triggered internally e.g. by HTTP endpoints or background processes.</p>

<h4>Event Types & Operations:</h4>

<table style='border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; margin: 10px 0;'>
<thead>
<tr style='background-color: #f5f5f5;'>
<th style='border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 8px; text-align: left;'>Event Type</th>
<th style='border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 8px; text-align: left;'>Incoming Payload Model</th>
<th style='border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 8px; text-align: left;'>Outgoing Payload Model</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
{%- for event_type_name, models in event_types.items() %}
<tr>
<td style='border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 8px;'><code>{{ event_type_name }}</code></td>
<td style='border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 8px;'><code>{% if models.incoming %}{{ models.incoming.__name__ }}{% else %}-{% endif %}</code></td>
<td style='border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 8px;'><code>{{ models.outgoing.__name__ }}</code></td>
</tr>
{%- endfor %}
</tbody>
</table>

<h4>Functionality:</h4>
<ul>
<li><strong>Send:</strong> Submit Event objects with appropriate payload models based on event type</li>
<li><strong>Receive:</strong> Get real-time events from other connected clients with validated payloads</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Channel:</strong> <code>{{ full_channel }}</code></p>
